Date: Wed, 16 Aug 2000 08:52:45 -0500
From: H. Larry Penning <bevpenn@fgi.net>
Source: El Diario de Hoy, El Salvador, Sabado 12 Ago 2000 [in Spanish
<http://www.elsalvador.com/noticias/EDICIONESANTERIORES/2000/AGOSTO/agosto12
/NACIONAL/> [Abstracted by JW

El Salvador - Suspected DHF deaths
----------------------------------
Six children have died from suspected dengue hemorrhagic fever in the last
two weeks; 3 more are in intensive care in Hospital Bloom.
*******
[2
Date: Sat, 19 Aug 2000 14:31:07 -0400
From: Marjorie P. Pollack <pollackmp@mindspring.com>
Source: Agencia EFE (vua COMTEX): filed: Fri Aug 18, 2000 5:51 PM EST [edited

Honduras - 3000 Classic Dengue Fever Cases Reported This Year
-------------------------------------------------------------
On Friday [18 Aug the Honduran Health Ministry confirmed 4 new cases of
hemorrhagic dengue fever, raising the total number of these cases to 8,
while 3000 new cases of classic dengue fever have been reported this year.
Marco Antonio Pinel, head of the Department of Epidemic Control, said that
of the 4 new cases of hemorrhagic dengue fever, 2 were reported in
Tegucigalpa and the others in the Eastern province of Olancho. According to
Pinel, none of the 8 cases of hemorrhagic dengue fever this year has proved
fatal. A nationwide prevention campaign is set to begin on 28 Aug 2000 to
eradicate breeding grounds of the vector of this disease, the _Aedes
egypti_ mosquito.
*******
[3
Date: Sat, 19 Aug 2000 14:31:07 -0400
From: Marjorie P. Pollack <pollackmp@mindspring.com>
Source: La Nacion, San Jose, Costa Rica, Saturday 19 Aug 2000 [edited

Joint action declaration to combat the spread of Dengue/DHF
------------------------------------------------------------
The Ministers of Health of several Central American countries [Costa Rica,
El Salvador, Guatemala and Honduras and Nicaragua attended a meeting in
the colonial city of Antigua, 45 km to the west of the Guatemalan capital
[and issued a declaration for implementation of joint action to contain the
spread of the epidemic now raging in the region.
According to statistics issued by the Ministry of Health of El Salvador, as
of last Wednesday there were 1216 cases of dengue reported in the country.
Of these, 149 were the hemorrhagic form, which had caused the loss of life
of 10 children and an adult since last January.
The Guatemalan Minister of Health said that in his country one child had
died of dengue hemorrhagic fever, and they had confirmed 3 more ill [with
DHF. In the present year they have detected 3500 cases of classical dengue
fever.
*******
[4
Date: 21 Aug 2000
From: ProMED-mail
Source: Xinhua news agency, 18 Aug 2000 [edited

Honduras - additional cases of Dengue/DHF
-----------------------------------------
The Honduran Health Ministry has confirmed 4 more cases of hemorrhagic
dengue fever (DHF), raising the number to 8 recorded this year, a Ministry
official said Friday. Two of the 4 cases were registered in Tegucigalpa
[the capital, and the other 2 in the Eastern Department of Olancho, said
Epidemiology Department chief Marco Antonio Pinel. None of the 8 persons
with the fatal disease has died, he said.
Pinel said some 3000 cases of dengue have been registered this year, 6000
less than in 1999. He also announced that on 28 Aug 2000 the government
will launch a nationwide campaign to eradicate water pools, where the
_Aedes aegypti_ mosquito transmitting the dengue virus breeds.
